  "keywords": [],
  "notes": [
    "We usually take with us a small jar of salt, and small mills with black pepper and chili flakes. Spices in hotels are usually very old, and sometimes there are none at all. ",
    "If there's no cooking oil of any kind, feel free to use butter."
  ],
  "overnight": false,
  "slug": "travelers-pasta",
  "steps": [
    {
      "name": "",
      "steps": [
        {
          "text": "Put a pot of generously salted water to boil.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Prepare the vegetables. **Onion:** peel, halve, and cut into 1/2 cm slices. **Garlic:** peel and roughly chop. **Chili:** remove the seeds, and cut as thing as possible. **Bell peppers:** remove the seeds, and roughly chop. **Zucchini:** remove the ends, halve lengthwise, and cut into 1/2 half-moons. **Cherry tomatoes:** halve. **Olives:** halve lengthwise.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "In a pan set on medium heat with olive oil or butter, sauté onions, chili, and garlic, until the onions are transparent.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the zucchini to the pan, and cook for a few minutes.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the bell pepper to the pan, and cook until the zucchini has softened but is still a bit crunchy.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "When the water starts to boil, add the pasta, and cook for 1-2 minutes less than recommended on a package.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Save one cup of pasta water, and discard the rest. Put the pot with the pasta back on the stove, and reduce the heat to medium-low.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the tomato sauce to the pasta (use a bit of pasta water to rinse the jar, and add this to the pasta too).",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the cherry tomatoes, the olives, and the vegetables to the pasta, and thoroughly mix everything. Add more salt if needed, and add black pepper and chili flakes. Cook for a few minutes to warm up all the ingredients and finish cooking the pasta.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add pieces of cheese to the pasta, mix thoroughly, and serve.",
          "pause": false
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
